From 52240506d610536ba0ed9c8bb2c34d5ef7f4f812 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 16:36:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] init: tolerate an existing /dev/kmsg node in LogInit
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Under the hybris_generic native chainload boot, init runs chrooted into
system_a and the chainload's initramfs has already created /dev/kmsg.
LogInit's mknod then fails with EEXIST and OpenLogDevice is skipped, so
init produces no kmsg logging for the rest of boot. Treat EEXIST as
success — the node we need is already there.

Change-Id: I54c9ec90407e700a894c1b3916629351962de258
Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 services/init/standard/init.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/services/init/standard/init.c b/services/init/standard/init.c
index 7009f47c..57bda3a0 100755
--- a/services/init/standard/init.c
+++ b/services/init/standard/init.c
@@ -123,7 +123,7 @@ void LogInit(void)
 {
     int ret = mknod("/dev/kmsg", S_IFCHR | S_IWUSR | S_IRUSR,
         makedev(MEM_MAJOR, DEV_KMSG_MINOR));
-    if (ret == 0) {
+    if (ret == 0 || errno == EEXIST) {
         OpenLogDevice();
     }
 }
